A backlog is a prioritized list of work.

A product backlog is the main list of work for the project.

Example:

  Build login page
  
  Create homepage
  
  Add map markers
  
  Fix search bug
  
  Add user profile



A portfolio backlog is for bigger work.

It groups smaller tasks under larger goals.

Example:

  Epic: Build User Account System
  
  Feature: Login
  
  Feature: Signup
  
  Feature: Profile Page


Backlog Priority

  The order of the backlog matters.

  Items at the top are usually more important.


